Paper: hep-th/0103171

Date: 2001-03-21

Title: Deconstructing de Sitter

Authors: Vijay Balasubramanian, Petr Horava, and Djordje Minic

Comments: 17 pages, LaTe, v2.

Journal-ref: JHEP 0105 (2001) 043

Semiclassical gravity predicts that de Sitter space has a finite entropy. Wesuggest a picture for Euclidean de Sitter space in string theory, and use theAdS/CFT correspondence to argue that de Sitter entropy can be understood as thenumber of degrees of freedom in a quantum mechanical dual.